definition.value: A 1-acyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine where the 1-O-acyl group is specified as palmitoyl and the linoleoyl group has (14)C labels at the C-1 position.
A glycodihydroceramide having an alpha-D-glucuronic acid residue at the O-1 position and a tetradecanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A glycosylmannose consisting of an beta-D-galactosyl residue attached to alpha-D-mannose at the 3-position.
The amino hexadecasaccharide obtained when four molecules of the repeating tetrasacchride unit from Shigella dysenteriae O-specific polysaccharide are joined via alpha-(1->3) linkages.

An acylglycerophosphocholine resulting from partial hydrolysis of a phosphatidylcholine, which removes one of the fatty acyl groups. The structure is depicted in the image where R1 = acyl, R2 = H or where R1 = H, R2 = acyl.
A 1,2,4-triazolo[3,4-a]phthalazine having a methyl substituent at the 3-position.
An hydroxamate siderophore produced by several fungal species.
An organic heterotricyclic compound comprising a triazole ring fused to a phthalazine ring system.
An amino pentasaccharide epitope consisting of three 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulose residues and two N-acetylglucosamine residues (one at the reducing end) in a linear sequence.
A glycosylphosphatidylinositol having two D-mannosyl groups as the glycosyl moieties; obtained via extraction of the cell wall of Mycobacterium bovis.
A glycosylphosphatidylinositol having a pentamannose moiety of unspecified composition as the glycosyl fragment; obtained via extraction of the cell wall of Mycobacterium bovis.
Any trehalose bearing a single O-mycolate substituent; obtained via extraction of the cell wall of Mycobacterium bovis.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the anion of adenosylcobinamide guanosyl diphosphate with overall charge -1, arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Monoanion of cob(I)alamin arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of magnesium 13(1)-hydroxyprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17.  It is  the principal species at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of phenylureas that is 1,1-dimethylurea substituted by a p-cumenyl group at position 3. A selective, systemic herbicide used to control annual grasses and broadleaf weeds in cereals, its use within the EU has been banned after September 2017 on the grounds of potential groundwater contamination and risks to aquatic life; there have also been concerns about its endocrine-disrupting properties.
The conjugate base of magnesium 13(1)-oxoprotoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of magnesium protoporphyrin 13-monomethyl ester, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl group at C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of magnesium protoporphyrin, formed by deprotonation of the carboxyethyl groups at C-13 and C-17. It is the principal species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of adenosylcobalamin 5'-phosphate, formed by loss of two protons from the 5'-phosphate group.
The anion of 5-hydroxybenzimidazolylcob(I)amide, formed by loss of a proton from the phosphate OH group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A polysaccharide derivative composed of a backbone of beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-L-Rha repeating units that are joined to each other via alpha-(1->3)-linkages; corresponds to the repeating unit of the O-polysaccharide from Pasteurella haemolytica serotypes 3 and 15.

A polysaccharide derivative composed of a backbone of linear trisaccharide derivative repeating units that are joined to each other via beta-(1->4)-linkages; corresponds to the repeating unit of the O-polysaccharide from Pasteurella haemolytica serotypes 1, 6 and 9.

A polysaccharide composed of a backbone of alpha-galactopyranosyl-(1->3)-galactofuranosyl repeating units that are joined to each other via beta-(1->4)-linkages; corresponds to the repeating unit of the O-polysaccharide from Pasteurella haemolytica serotypes 4 and 10.
The anion formed from 6-methyl-7-oxo-8-(1-D-ribityl)lumazine by removal of a proton from the nitrogen at position 3 (i.e. between the oxo groups). It is the major species at physiological pH.

P-cluster from Mo-independent nitrogenases, deprotonated to pH 7.3. Unfortunately, there are no structures available, and one of the O ligands of Fe has actually not been confirmed (hence the X in the name)
A homopolymer composed of poly(chloroprene) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of polycarbazole macromolecules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(2,9-carbazole)macromolecules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(1,8-carbazole) macromolecules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(3,6-carbazole) macromolecules.
A poly(3,6-carbazole) polymer, composed of poly(carbazole-3,6-diyl) macromolecules.
A poly(1,8-carbazole) polymer, composed of poly(carbazole-1,8-diyl) macromolcules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(indolo[3,2-b]carbazole)macromolecules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(3,9-carbazole) macromolecules.
A polycarbazole polymer, composed of poly(2,7-carbazole) macromolecules.
A poly(2,7-carbazole) polymer, composed of poly(carbazole-2,7-diyl) macromolecules.
A hybrid iron-sulfur-oxygen cluster in which four iron atoms are linked by two sulfur and two oxygen bridging ligands
A monomethoxyflavone that is quercetin in which the hydroxy group at position 3' is replaced by a methoxy group.
An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which unspecified alkyl and acyl groups are located at positions 1 and 2 respectively.
Any cation arising from protonation of at least one of the amino functions in an indole alkaloid.
The glycerophosphoglycerophosphate anion of charge -3 formed by loss of a 3 protons from the OH groups of the phosphate functions.
An ionic phospholipid that is the organophosphate oxoanion formed from phosphatidylglycerol by removal of a proton from the phosphate OH group.
The zwitterion formed by transfer of a proton from the OH of the phospho group to the alanyl amino nitrogen.
Molybdenum cofactor MoCo protonated to pH 7.3.
A homopolymer, composed of gamma-poly(glutamic acid) macromolecule.
Lysergol esterified with cyclohexanecarboxylic acid.

An alkaloid of the ergoline family that occurs as a minor constituent in some species of fungi and in the morning glory family of plants. Its structure is that of ergoline with a methyl group at N-6 and a beta-hydroxymethyl substituent at C-8.
One of a class of naturally occurring alkaloids with a structure based on that of ergoline.
